{"name":"Malediction: Infectious Affliction","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Prerequisite: 10th level, @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.wz9H5n7VgZhpvyBO]{Fecund Affliction}</p><p>When your affliction ends on a creature before its full duration has elapsed, you can use your reaction to attempt to afflict a different creature you can see within 30 feet of the previously afflicted creature.</p><p>The new target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become the sufferer of the affliction for its remaining duration.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/unholy/hand-light-green.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SCNVmesHA4LAjNsI"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674808992690,"modifiedTime":1674875628399,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"UN0sPcB5A5u8oCY2"}
{"name":"Ravenous Weapon","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 20th level, your curse armament can have up to two magic melee weapons consumed at the same time. If you attempt to feed it a third, it regurgitates your choice of one of the two weapons it currently has consumed.</p><p>If both of your curse armament’s consumed weapons grant a bonus to attack and damage rolls using the weapon, you use the higher of the two bonuses, not the combination. For example, if your curse weapon has consumed a weapon +2 and a weapon +3, you will receive a +3 bonus to your attack and damage rolls using your curse armament, not a +5 bonus.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Curse of the Armament","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"modules/jean-homebrew/images/warrior/Warriorskill_35.png","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WzPNcVQqoXvZdj3V"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674881567945,"modifiedTime":1674881808600,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Ug2orb4cwvLvKFE4"}
{"name":"Bone Spurring","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 1st level, you can work with your skeleton to form and expel armaments made from your bones. As an action, you can create a tool that weighs 10 lbs or less that you have proficiency with, one martial melee weapon, or a shield. The bone object appears in one of your empty hands, and you have proficiency with weapons and shields you create with this feature.</p><p>You can have a number of bone objects created with this feature equal to your curse ability modifier (minimum 1). If you attempt to create one beyond this number, your choice of one of the previous bone objects crumbles to powder.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"action","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Curse of Animation","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/death/bones-crossed-orange.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8FgHODFvh6kAAF6y"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674877021496,"modifiedTime":1674879133155,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"VGg9y15Jtl3W38Ku"}
{"name":"Necromantic Spurs","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 3rd level, each weapon you create with your Bone Spurring counts as magical for the purpose of overcoming resistance and immunity to nonmagical attacks and damage while you wield it.</p><p>Additionally, you can empower the bone objects you create with your curse’s animating energy. When you create an object with your Bone Spurring or as a bonus action while holding one of your bone objects, you can expend a spell slot to empower it until it leaves your hand. The empowered effect depends on the type of bone object.</p><p><strong>Shield.</strong> You gain an additional +1 bonus to AC while you wield the shield. You can gain this bonus from only one empowered bone shield at a time.</p><p><strong>Weapon.</strong> You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls you make with the weapon.</p><p><strong>Tool.</strong> You gain a +1 bonus to ability checks you make using the tool. </p><p>The bonus granted by an empowered bone object increases if you expend certain higher level spell slots to use this feature: to +2 if you use a spell slot of 3rd or 4th level, and to +3 if you use a spell slot of 5th level</p><p>or higher.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Curse of Animation","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/death/hand-undead-skeleton-fire-pink.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ARXQn63Wf7ebWTbI"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674878136986,"modifiedTime":1674879190855,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"VWhtscUq6D83Cmkj"}
{"name":"Malediction: Hostile Bane","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Your curse imbues your attacks with its dark magicks. Once during each of your turns when you hit a creature with an attack, you can cause the attack to deal additional necrotic damage equal to your curse ability modifier (minimum 1).</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-blade-knife-orange-blue.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OHuu9TLMkpkLgwrd"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674807929989,"modifiedTime":1674875552680,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Y7k2VZ9C90Qs03Uj"}
{"name":"Vitality Splint","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 15th level, you can use your skeleton’s animating energy to restore your own vitality. As an action, you can expend a spell slot to regain a number of your expended Hit Dice equal to the slot’s level.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Curse of Animation","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"modules/jean-homebrew/images/priest/Priestskill_24.png","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LYlpxQ80wBfHclRE"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674878961706,"modifiedTime":1674879263114,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"YpgK0ARqCPnXSiv5"}
{"name":"Calculated Combustion","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 11th level, you gain enough control over your flames that you can create pockets of safety within them for your companions. When you use an accursed class feature or cast an accursed spell that deals fire damage, you can choose a number of creatures you can see up to half your accursed level. Each of the chosen creatures automatically succeeds on any saving throw it makes against the feature or spell this turn, and takes no damage if it would normally take half damage on a successful save.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Curse of Combustion","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/fire/beam-jet-stream-embers.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WoHB1e6W7P9159IL"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674883144419,"modifiedTime":1674883598744,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"Z7RYTLGFZEwqDsZd"}
{"name":"Malediction: Vile Affliction","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Prerequisite: 18th level, @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.UN0sPcB5A5u8oCY2]{Infectious Affliction} or @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.cytca5kZTBqa9vqa]{Prolific Affliction}</p><p>You can use your Afflict as a bonus action on your turn. Additionally, when you use your Afflict, you can choose any number of your ailments. If a target fails its saving throw, it suffers each of the chosen ailments for the duration.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/earth/strike-body-stone-crumble.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nrHxp7FOtFmXpWBZ"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674812725789,"modifiedTime":1674875788364,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"a3Wsz6OmzW7zybNA"}
{"name":"Malediction: Prolific Affliction","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Prerequisite: 10th level, @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.wz9H5n7VgZhpvyBO]{Fecund Affliction}</p><p>When you spend a spell slot of 2nd-level or higher to use your Afflict, instead of increasing the affliction’s duration, you can choose an additional target for each slot level above 1st. If you do, each target that fails its saving throw is afflicted for 1 minute.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/unholy/orb-beam-pink.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gS1QI7jbbUbpPLcl"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674809361156,"modifiedTime":1674875667248,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"cytca5kZTBqa9vqa"}
{"name":"Ailment Control","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Starting at 2nd level, you can also use your spell slots to exert control over your curse’s ailments, either afflicting another creature with one of your ailments or suppressing your ailments’ effects on yourself. The duration of the effect depends on the level of the spell slot expended to use it: 1 minute for a 1st-level spell slot, 10 minutes for a 2nd-level, 1 hour for a 3rd-level, 8 hours for a 4th-level, or 24 hours for a spell slot of 5th-level or higher.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.B7zo4IlA8zKpaEId]{Afflict}</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.OQSxgGu4EW5xlmhK]{Supress}</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/holy/meditation-chi-focus-blue.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vRFKqheHZmQ1K8S8"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674801252135,"modifiedTime":1674803278404,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"diiGjf2wPSFG91zI"}
{"name":"Vampiric Weapon","type":"spell","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You imbue a weapon you touch with a thirst for blood. Until the spell ends, the weapon gains a +1 bonus to attack rolls and deals an extra [[/r 1d6]] necrotic damage on a hit. If the target of an attack made with the weapon attack isn’t an undead or construct, the weapon’s wielder regains a number of hit points equal to the necrotic damage dealt.</p><p>If the weapon isn’t already a magic weapon, it becomes one for the duration. If it is already magical when you cast this spell, and part of its magical properties is granting a bonus to attack rolls, you use your choice of either the weapon’s bonus or this spell’s, not the combination.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th or 7th level, the bonus to attack rolls increases to +2 and the extra damage increases to [[/r 2d6]]. When you use a spell slot of 8th level or higher, the bonus to attack rolls increases to +3 and the extra damage increases to [[/r 3d6]].</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":4,"school":"nec","components":{"vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"a vial of vampire blood, which you pour over the weapon","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"img":"icons/magic/death/weapon-sword-skull-purple.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8K9PrRCF7mkf3OPi"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674880671946,"modifiedTime":1674880820684,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"eHFcpoNzLQaAiLGs"}
{"name":"Malediction: Instinctual Suppression","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Prerequisite: 10th level, @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.7qx0UlxvV9qkrRlg]{Bolstering Suppression}</p><p>When you roll initiative, you can use your reaction to use your Suppress. If you do, you gain a +4 bonus to your AC until the end of your next turn. You can take this reaction even if you are surprised.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"reaction","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":"","recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-deflect-teal.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vMBcvY4Dr1otFE69"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674809129230,"modifiedTime":1674875632712,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"emMU9jJhbTuPWRss"}
{"name":"Malediction: Doubling Jinx","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>Prerequisite: 18th level, @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.y7eD8cy1hmZgE8Qk]{Enervating Jinx} or @UUID[Compendium.jean-homebrew.accursed.OulSr1GPhsibyjhz]{Startling Jinx}</p><p>When you use your Jinx, you can target a second creature within range. If both targets fail their Wisdom saving throw against the feature, you can choose a different jinx for each target.</p><p>If neither jinxed target makes the associated type of roll before the end of your next turn, you can use the same action to maintain both jinxes, given that the jinx hasn’t ended for another reason and you are able to maintain the jinx.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/unholy/projectiles-binary-pink.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.IvZfmssNCOqVHJU6"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674811445703,"modifiedTime":1674875717506,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"fZlLl1AfqKpQ47Qg"}
{"name":"Spellcasting","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<p>At 2nd level, you learn to use your curse’s vile magicks to fuel the casting of spells. See Chapter 10 in the Player’s Handbook for the general rules of spellcasting.</p><h2>Spell Slots</h2><p>The Accursed table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level and higher. To cast one of these spells, you must expend a spell slot of the spell’s level or higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.</p><h2>Curse Spells</h2><p>Each Conquered Curse has a list of spells — its curse spells — that you learn when you reach certain levels in this class, as shown in the curse description. These spells are added to the accursed spell list for you and are included in the number in the Spells Known column of the Accursed table. You ignore the material component requirement of a curse spell if it has one.</p><h2>Spells Known of 1st Level and Higher</h2><p>You know the curse spell you gain at 2nd level from your Conquered Curse, and one 1st-level spell of your choice from the accursed spell list, for a total of two spells known.</p><p>The Spells Known column of the Accursed table shows when you learn more spells of your choice from the accursed spell list. Each of these spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, when you reach 5th level in this class, you learn one new spell of 1st or 2nd level, in addition to the curse spell you gain at 5th level from your Conquered Curse.</p><p>Additionally, when you gain a level in this class, you can choose one of the accursed spells you know — which can be one of your curse spells — and replace it with another spell from the accursed spell list, which must also be of a level for which you have spell slots.</p><h2>Spellcasting Ability</h2><p>Your curse ability is your spellcasting ability for your accursed spells, since your ability to cast spells comes from the control you have over your curse’s power. You use your curse ability whenever a spell refers to your spellcasting ability. In addition, you use your curse ability modifier when setting the saving throw DC for an accursed spell you cast and when making an attack roll with one.</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Spell save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your curse ability modifier</p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Spell attack modifier</strong> = your proficiency bonus + your curse ability modifier</p><h2>Spellcasting Focus</h2><p>When you gain this feature, choose arcane foci, druidic foci, or holy symbols, depending on how you discovered to channel your curse. You can use the chosen type of implement or a cursed object as a spellcasting focus (found in chapter 5 of the Player’s Handbook) for your accursed spells.</p><h2>Accursed Spell List</h2><p>Here’s the list of spells you consult when you learn an accursed spell. The list is organized by spell level, not character level. Many of these spells are from the Player’s Handbook. If a spell’s name is followed by the XGE superscript, the spell can be found in Xanathar’s Guide to Everything. Additionally, spells with the UAH superscript are original spells that can be found in Chapter 4: Feats &amp; Spells.</p>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"UAH","activation":{"type":"","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":"","units":""},"cover":null,"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"","attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"type":{"value":"class","subtype":""},"requirements":"Accursed","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"icons/magic/lightning/bolt-strike-hand-gray.webp","effects":[],"ownership":{"default":0,"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SZV0TEfAjb4ucnMy"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.1.2","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1674800494372,"modifiedTime":1674813376006,"lastModifiedBy":"B0DJHUzhCGludWuM"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"_id":"hWHDxIl3JQN2r1Nw"}
